90b667eeb181328b4aae31d43e9c2658cbd181df.summary: **The chain refactor -- no commit message can tell of the horror** This commit message encapsulates a ~6000 line change, so this message will only scratch the surface.  The chain-manager has been refactored into three distinct modules: the chain syncer, the chain store, and consensus.  Consensus is a stateless module that runs validation and weight calculation on input tipsets and states.  The chain store keeps the validated chain safe, notifies subscribers about changes to the head, and offers access to the chain structure.  There's a read only version that most modules use.  #principle-of-least- priviledge.  The chain syncer has the only writable reference into the store. The syncer gets new blocks and chains of blocks from the network and updates the chain store with blocks it finds that satisfy the consensus rules.  The syncer tries not to get DOSed but these are early days.
